<HEADLINE>
BRUINS HIT BY ILLNESS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   An upper respiratory infection is doing what Oregon tailback
Reuben Droughns could not _ running through UCLA's defensive line.
</P>
<P>
   End Kenyon Coleman and tackle Ken Kocher were two of six Bruins
who didn't practice Wednesday because of infection. End Rusty
Williams and reserve tackle Steve Morgan are also sick, but they
practiced.
</P>
<P>
   In all, 21 Bruins have symptoms ranging from sinus congestion to
sore throats, coughing and fever. But so far, only reserve guard Ed
Anderson (pneumonia) has been ruled out of Saturday's game against
Cal.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a virus going through the community at large,'' Bruins
athletic trainer Geoff Schaadt said.
</P>
<P>
   It hit UCLA late last week. According to coach Bob Toledo, 12
players were sick before the Oregon game, some with high fevers,
but everyone played.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's like a flu epidemic, and it's not flu season _ that's
what worries me,'' Toledo said. ``We told them to be careful about
sucking on bottles and (to) isolate themselves from people who have
it.''
</P>
<P>
   Foster update: Although tailback DeShaun Foster (sprained ankle)
hasn't been ruled out for the Oct.23 game at Oregon State, it's
unlikely he'll risk extensive damage on OSU's AstroTurf.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's new turf, and it looks good, but it's still turf,''
Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   Foster, who won't play this week, could return for the Oct.30
showdown with Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Secondary switch: Reserve cornerback Lovell Houston has switched
to safety to better suit his skills and UCLA's needs.
</P>
<P>
   A redshirt freshman, Houston has been hurt for most of his 14
months on campus and needs to learn the defense and add strength
before he becomes a full-time player. He was unable to participate
in the weight program last year because of operations on both
shoulders.
</P>
<P>
   Catching up with: Former UCLA center Shawn Stuart is teaching at
a private school in San Jose.
</P>
<P>
   Ex-guard Andy Meyers was cut by the Buffalo Bills and is selling
real estate in L.A.
</P>
<P>
   Former kicker Chris Sailer is finishing his degree and working
for the football office and Fox Sports West.
</P>
<P>
   Former quarterback Cade McNown makes the first start of his NFL
career Sunday when his Chicago Bears play Philadelphia. (Bears
starter Shane Matthews is hurt.)
</P>
<P>
   Ex-coach Terry Donahue, currently assisting Bill Walsh with the
San Francisco 49ers, became a grandfather Tuesday. His oldest
daughter, Nicole, gave birth to Brooke Alexandra at 2 a.m. in
Newport Beach.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-14-99 0133EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
