<HEADER>
A6673 &Cx1f; tad-z
r k BC-COMMENTARY-BJT15-COX     10-14 0766
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Friday, October 15, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   EDIT-NUKE _ Politics used to stop at the water's edge. Not with
this Congress, especially its most rabid isolationists and
Clintonphobes. They have deluded themselves into thinking now the
Cold War is over, they can be as irresponsbile as they please.
That's the message of the test ban treaty defeat. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDIT-RAMSEY _ No one is happy with the outcome of the Ramsey
grand jury, but we have to accept the decision. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ Pius XII is a candidate for
beatification, a step away from sainthood. His candidacy has been
sharply challenged by a new book, ``Hitler's Pope,'' in which Pius
emerges as a figure less saintly than just human. (Rosenfeld, Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ Just in case you weren't feeling too old
today, this may certainly change things. According to an e-mail I
received, each year, the staff at Beloit College in Wisconsin puts
together a list to try to give the faculty a sense of the mindset
of that year's incoming freshmen. Here is this year's list that was
sent to me. (Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily
News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ ``Texas Constitution 2000'' is a small group of
people with a big idea: persuade 176 out of 254 counties in the
state to ratify a roughly 20-page proposed state constitution to
replace the present document. Why 176 counties? Because the
proportion of 176 out of 254 is the same percentage as the nine of
13 colonies that were required to ratify the U.S. Constitution.
(Gary Borders is editor and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily
Sentinel.) EMBARGOED for Sunday. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The Mexican press, so timid in
criticizing government for so long, is flexing editorial muscle.
(Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of the Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ It's always a gift to state
representatives when a state senator chooses to resign in midterm
rather than simply not run for re-election. The early resignation
gives them a shot at moving up to the Texas Senate without giving
up their House seats. Sen. Greg Luna (D-San Antonio), who has
represented the center-city 26th District since 1992, resigned
Sept. 24 for health reasons. (McNeely, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ They came from all over the country
_ authors, scientists, scholars. They jammed reams of research and
analysis into two days, all focused on a riveting modern-day
discovery: Christianity and environmentalism: Same thing! (John
Young is opinion page editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
