A6864 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-MOVIE-SIEGRFRIED15-CO     10-14 0393
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-SIEGRFRIED15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eye-popping Imax magic in 3-D
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Welcome to Cirque du Surreal.
</P>
<P>
   Siegfried and Roy _ those hocus-pocus Las Vegas glam guys _ have
a 3-D Imax movie, and it isn't hype to say you have to see it to
believe it.
</P>
<P>
   For a full 51 minutes, this duo is in your face in ``Siegfried &AMP;
Roy: The Magic Box,'' doing their sleight-of-hand thing. Making
elephants disappear. Having furry white tigers leap over your head.
Waving 6-foot wands near your ears. Trotting out a lineup of Vegas
babes tarted up in golden armor.
</P>
<P>
   It's a dumbfoundingly watchable movie, girded like some weird
Wagnerian opera with giant metal dragons spewing fire and
long-haired male assistants strutting their stuff in chiseled body
suits. Obviously, the concept of garish didn't die with Liberace.
</P>
<P>
   But there's more.
</P>
<P>
   Beyond the Las Vegas stage, ``Siegfried &AMP; Roy'' gives a couple
of peeks inside their lavish private digs. Their home is crammed
with tapestries, Thai statues and beveled glass. Roy seems to like
to sprawl on a huge, cushiony bed with one of his powder-puffy
white tigers, both surrounded by dozens of lighted candles.
</P>
<P>
   But there's more.
</P>
<P>
   This movie also looks back, pulling Siegfried and Roy's life
stories from some magical neverland. We see scenes of a young
Siegfried dazzling his father in Germany with a simple magic trick
using a coin, a handkerchief and a glass. Roy got his start working
at a zoo in Bremen, frolicking with a cheetah in and out of its
cage.
</P>
<P>
   These two apparently hooked up on an ocean liner, doing
eye-popping magical bits and eventually being lured to Vegas by an
entrepreneur mesmerized by their act.
</P>
<P>
   With ``The Magic Box,'' these magicians have fashioned for
themselves the perfect mash note. Why else do we keep seeing
audiences leap to their feet for standing ovations and shouts of
bravo?
</P>
<P>
   The film's content is all mirrors, illusions and smoke.
</P>
<P>
   Just beware that in 3-D, smoke sure gets in your eyes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Siegfried &AMP; Roy:
</P>
<P>
   The Magic Box''
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   In 3-D. Featuring Siegfried Fischbacher and Roy Uwe Ludwig Horn.
Narrated by Anthony Hopkins. Directed by Brett Leonard.
</P>
<P>
   51 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Verdict: Glitz and glam hocus-pocus.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
