1 of a playoff series on a Bernie Williams extra-inning home run.
In 1996, it was young Jeffrey Maier reaching over the right-field
wall to turn Derek Jeter's long fly ball into a home run, with
umpire Richie Garcia failing to call fan interference. Last night,
it was umpire Rick Reed ruling that Chuck Knoblauch had held onto a
throw to second base in the top of the 10th inning, when he clearly
hadn't. By Buster Olney.
