<P>
   NY-LATINO (New York) _ The recent blast of popular enthusiasm
for Latino music and culture has yet to find serious resonance in
the mainstream New York art world. People of Hispanic descent now
make up nearly 30 percent of the city's population, but most of its
high-profile museums seem to have slept through that development,
and only a handful of galleries regularly show Latino artists. This
situation automatically makes El Museo del Barrio an indispensable
public resource. By Holland Cotter.
</P>
