<P>
   COLORADO-EDUCATION. Congressman Tom Tancredo is pushing
legislation that would alter bilingual education. How will it
affect the community of Pueblo, in which many Hispanics live? (500
words.) By Tania Anderson
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT-SUB-STAMPS. Like the vessels they are commemorating,
submarine postage stamps have risen from the depths of the reject
pile at the Postal Service and will be in use next March, Rep. Sam
Gejdenson said Thursday. (550 words.) By Jill Carroll
</P>
<P>
   IDAHO-CLINTON-LAND. Idaho lawmakers said President Clinton's
plan to preserve 40 million acres of federal forest land would be
harmful to Idaho communities. (650 words.) By Barney McManigal
</P>
<P>
   ILLINOIS-DCJOURNAL. A look inside the Illinois congressional
delegation this week. (400 words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
