researcher Thursday said the National Institutes of Health is not
spending enough on diabetes research. (800 words.) By Jill Carroll
</P>
<P>
   NEW MEXICO-WORST-HUNGER. New statistics show New Mexico as the
worst state in the nation for ``food security'' - meaning how many
people have regular access to enough food. (400 words.) By Jonathan
Lipman
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-LAKE-LATOURETTE. Rep. Steven C. LaTourette warned members
of the International Joint Commission on Thursday against the bulk
sale of water from the Great Lakes, referring to the lakes as a
``liquid gold mine.'' (375 words.) By Sean Gorman
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-SPACE. Space Access, a space launch company that many in
Texas hope will choose to build a spaceport in the Rio Grande
Valley, is waiting for federal agencies to approve the site before
it decides, a spokesman said. The Texas delegation wrote a letter
to the company this week emphasizing why Texas would be a good
site. (500 words.) By Alex Canizares
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-CAMPAIGN. The Senate kicked off five days of debate
Thursday about campaign finance reform legislation sponsored by
Sens. Russ Feingold, D-Wis., and John McCain, R-Ariz. With a
scaled-back bill that focuses on banning so-called soft money
contributions, Feingold and McCain are hoping to win the first
battle in their war on what they consider a campaign finance system
that is out of control. (15 inches.) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
