   BBA-BOSTON-NY _ NEW YORK _ Coverage of Game 2 of the ALCS,
Boston at New York, 8:15 p.m. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-NOTES _ ALCS notebook. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES _ ATLANTA _ Everything appears to favor the Braves as
the NLCS shifts to New York for Friday's Game 3. The Braves have a
2-0 lead in the series, they have won 11 of 14 games against the
Mets this season and Game 3 starter Tom Glavine has won all three
of his decisions against New York. Despite those facts, the Braves
are not overconfident against the Mets and one of the newest
members, Brian Jordan, offered a dose of reality - he was a member
of the 1996 St. Louis Cardinal team which lost a 3-1 lead to the
Braves in the NLCS. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-NOTES _ NLCS notebook. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
