_ actually was a model of how researchers should recruit
African-Americans for clinical research. During a conference in
Atlanta Thursday on African-Americans and AIDS, Emory minority
health expert Stephen Thomas spoke of the positive lessons to be
learned from the Tuskegee syphilis study, and how those lessons
should be applied to fighting the HIV epidemic among blacks. (Kim,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
