against the Boston Red Sox on Thursday. The Bronx Bombers lead the
best-of-7 series 1-0. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-6, 10-14
-- Pitcher Ramon Martinez of the Boston Red Sox in action during
the first inning of Game 2 of the American League Championship
Series against the New York Yankees on Thursday. The Bronx Bombers
lead the best-of-7 series 1-0. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) LOS ANGELES -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- WHISTLEBLOWER-MOVIE,
10-14 -- The private life of Jeffrey S. Wigand as a tobacco
executive went public when he became a whistle-blower. Wigand is
now the center of public attention as ``Insider,'' a tale of how
``60 Minutes'' turned him away, comes to theaters. (Wade Spees/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-5, 10-14
-- Holy Cow, I think he's gonna throw it! Derek Jeter of the New
York Yankees looks on as Yankee Hall-of-Famer Phil Rizutto gets set
to throw the ``first pitch'' before Game 2 of the American League
Championship Series against the Boston Red Sex on Thursday. The
Yankees lead the best-of-7 series 1-0. (Barton Silverman/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- TYCO-SELLOFF, 10-14 -- L.
Dennis Kozlowski, Tyco International's chief, says he was outraged
by a ``false and baseless'' report attacking the company's
accounting practices. Investors brushed aside Tyco's aggressive
defense of its actions Thursday, pushing its stock down amid fears
about the company's three-year acquisition spree. (Angel Franco/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-4, 10-14
-- Derek Lowe of the Boston Red Sox chatting with some fans in the
outfield stands during practice before Game 2 of the American
League Championship Series against the New York Yankees on
Thursday. The Yankees lead the best-of-7 series 1-0. (Bill
Greene/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-3, 10-14
-- From left, Riche Garces, Pedro Martinez and Jose Offerman of the
Boston Red Sox fooling around during practice before Game 2 of the
American League Championship Series against the New York Yankees on
Thursday. The Yankees lead the best-of-7 series 1-0. (Bill
Greene/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) NEW YORK -- Oct. 14, 1999 -- BBA-YANKS-REDSOX-2, 10-14
-- New York Yankees manager Joe Torre, left, and his Boston Red Sox
counterpart, Jimmy Williams, before Game 2 of the American League
Championship Series against the Boston Red Sex at Yankee Stadium on
Thursday. (Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
