   BC-JONBENET-RAMSEY-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Oct. 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Oct.
13, about a grand jury's decision not to return indictments in the
death of JonBenet Ramsey referred incorrectly in some copies to the
Colorado Governor who raised the possibility last year of
appointing a special prosecutor in the case. It was Roy Romer, not
the current Governor, Bill Owens.
</P>
