QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-COLLEGE-LIFE-COURSES-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Go to class as much as possible. Yes, you're going to be
tired. If the professor sees you every day, then if you have to
leave early to catch a bus, or miss class, they might understand.''
</P>
<P>
   _ERIN LAYTON, a University of Connecticut graduate student
lecturing underclassmen in ``Life Skills for Athletes.''
</P>
